## Plan Summary

After thorough exploration of the codebase, here's the complete implementation plan — **only `common/chat.cpp` is modified**.

---

### Two additions to `common/chat.cpp`:

#### 1. New static handler function (insert before line 1634)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
    const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        if (msg.value("role", "") == "system") {
            system_prompt = msg.value("content", "");
            break;
        }
    }

    bool first_user_processed = false;
    data.prompt = "<s>";

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            continue;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (!first_user_processed && !system_prompt.empty()) {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + system_prompt + "\n" + content + " [/INST]";
            } else {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
            first_user_processed = true;
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

#### 2. Detection logic (insert after GigaChatV3 block, before `return std::nullopt` at line 1690)

```cpp
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

---

### Key design decisions:
- Uses **`COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY`** with manual prompt building (no PEG parser, no Jinja rendering — unlike other handlers)
- System message is extracted in a **first pass**, then prepended to the first user turn
- Detection requires `[INST]` + `[/INST]` **present** AND `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` **absent** — safely distinguishes from the existing Ministral-3 handler
- `common/chat.h` is **not touched**
